messages.content: ComfyUI_StreamDiffusion is an implementation of StreamDiffusion for ComfyUI, which is a pipeline-level solution for real-time interactive generation using diffusion-based image generation techniques.
Who are the authors of StreamDiffusion?
The authors of StreamDiffusion are Akio Kodaira, Chenfeng Xu, Toshiki Hazama, Takanori Yoshimoto, Kohei Ohno, Shogo Mitsuhori, Soichi Sugano, Hanying Cho, Zhijian Liu, and Kurt Keutzer.
To use ComfyUI_StreamDiffusion, you can download the workflow image provided and import it into ComfyUI.
Yes, img2img can be done in ComfyUI_StreamDiffusion by sending an image to the image input in the sampler node, but the batch_size must be 1.
Is Input Latent implemented in StreamDiffusion_Sampler?
No, Input Latent is not implemented in StreamDiffusion_Sampler for now.
How can you set Lora stack in ComfyUI_StreamDiffusion?
You can set Lora stack in ComfyUI_StreamDiffusion by using LoRA Stacker from Efficiency Nodes.
What are the performance enhancements introduced by StreamDiffusion?
StreamDiffusion introduces significant performance enhancements to current diffusion-based image generation techniques, enabling real-time interactive generation.
